'''''Bashville''''' is a British musical adapted by David William and Benny Green from George Bernard Shaw's play ''[[The Admirable Bashville]]'', with music by [[Denis King]] and lyrics by Benny Green. It was originally produced at the [[Regent's Park Open Air Theatre]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://openairtheatreheritage.com/productions/bashville/Vq-IOycAACgA3bbf|title=Bashville (1983) {{!}} Our Heritage {{!}} Open Air Theatre|website=openairtheatreheritage.com|language=en|access-date=2017-03-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/on-the-record-ethel-mermans-balloon-and-bashville-com-128068|title=ON THE RECORD: Ethel Merman's 'Balloon' and Bashville {{!}} Playbill|website=Playbill|language=en|access-date=2017-03-03}}</ref>

''Bashville'' was nominated for [[Laurence Olivier Award for Best New Musical|Best New Musical]] at the [[1983 Laurence Olivier Awards|1983 Olivier Awards]].

